To use environment variables in a component, you can use the `process.env` object, which allows you to access all environment variables defined in your project's `.env` file. 

For example, if you have a `.env` file with a variable called `MY_VAR`, you can access it in a component like this:

```
const myVar = process.env.MY_VAR;

return (
  <div>
    <h1>{myVar}</h1>
  </div>
);
```

Make sure to prefix your environment variable names with `REACT_APP_` so that they can be read by Create React App. For example, `REACT_APP_MY_VAR`.

Also, keep in mind that environment variables are loaded at build time, so if you change an environment variable, you'll need to rebuild your app to see the changes take effect.

